<p>As a Paladin, you start with 10 hit points plus your constitution modifier.
<input type="hidden" name="char_class" value="Paladin">
<input type="hidden" name="hit_point_max" value="10">
<p>You are proficient in all armor and shields.</p>
<input type="hidden" name="prof[armor]" value="All Armor">
<input type="hidden" name="prof[armor]" value="Shields">
<p>You are proficient with simple and martial weapons.</p>
<input type="hidden" name="prof[wep]" value="simple weapons">
<input type="hidden" name="prof[wep]" value="martial weapons">
<p>You are proficient in saving throws of wisdom and charisma.</p>
<input type="hidden" name="skill" value="wis_sav">
<input type="hidden" name="skill" value="cha_sav">
<p>Choose two of the following skills</p>
<select 
  ng-options="skills as skills for skills in ctrl.selectedCharClass.possible_skills track by skills"
  ng-model="ctrl.charClassSkillsSelected"
  name="skill"
  multiple>
</select>
<p>You start with the following weapons</p>
<select
  ng-options="weapon as weapon for weapon in ctrl.selectedCharClass.wep_one track by weapon"
  ng-model="ctrl.charWep1Selected"
  name="equip[wep]"
></select>
<select
  ng-options="weapon2 as weapon2 for weapon2 in ctrl.selectedCharClass.wep_two track by weapon2"
  ng-model="ctrl.charWep2Selected"
  name="equip[wep]"
></select>
<select
  ng-options="weapon3 as weapon3 for weapon3 in ctrl.selectedCharClass.wep_three track by weapon3"
  ng-model="ctrl.charWep3Selected"
  name="equip[wep]"
></select>

<p>You also start with the one of these packs</p>
<select
  ng-options="option as option for option in ctrl.selectedCharClass.opt_one track by option"
  ng-model="ctrl.charOpt1Selected"
  name="equip[gen]"
></select>

<p>You also start with Chain Mail and a Holy Symbol</p>
<input type="hidden" name="equip[armor]" value="Chain Mail">
<input type="hidden" name="equip[gen]" value="Holy Symbol">

<p>As a Paladin, you have the ability Divine Sense, meaning whenever you want you can open your awareness to detect good and evil, and until the next turn you will know the location of any celestial, fiend, undead within 60 feet of you. You are also aware of any presence of any object that has been consecrated or desecrated. You can do this as many times as 1+ your charisma modifier. You regain your uses at the end of a long rest.</p>
<input type="hidden" name="features", value="Divine Sense">

<p>You also have the ability Lay on Hands, letting you heal with your touch. You can restore a total number of hit points equal to your paladin level times 5. You can touch any creature and restore hit points up to the total you have. You can restore this with a long rest</p>
<input type="hidden" name="features" value="Lay on Hands">